content: Really helps me keep up up with all my symptoms.

The app so far has been easy to use. I've appear to have gotten allergic to something and have been utilizing the app to track my food and enter symptoms. As more data is entered I'll end up with a better picture. Only fault I have is I wish the barcode system was able to detect items more frequently. So far nothing I've tried has scanned. You can manually enter items and ingredients but this becomes time consuming in the grand scheme.
Great app 👌

Above & beyond excellent! I have been using this app since 2010. it allows me to to record everything including recipes so I don't have to keep typing out the ingredients each time. It gives clear indications of what foods might be disagreeing with me but also allows me to register things like sleep quality and mood. It also has a useful function that allows you to to send a spreadsheet or a PDF of your recordings by email. If you need help the support is second to none!
I don't seem to be able to add ingredients. Annoying.
I've been tracking my eating and digestive habits to see what could be contributing to my digestive issues. Was able to show to my gastroenterologist as well. Reminders come in handy and notes too.
Thorough and customizable.
Good so far
Awesome app. The only downside is that it drains my battery on my phone, otherwise I would've given 5 stars. That goes 4 both the original & lite version
Easy to use. Sometimes confusing when adding new product then also needing to add a new category get an error. Still not sure I am understanding the relationship analysis correctly.
Nothing can be scanned. Inconvenient to have to add everything manually.
Excellent app,takes a little getting used to that's the only reason for 4 stars

Really appreciating all the options this app has to make it easy to journal your food, symptoms, and other environmental factors, and then putting them all together for you. Can't believe this is free!
Great app, exactly what I've been looking for.
Very easy to use, well designed app
Great app for logging food, symptoms and sleep. Best I've found, easy and intuitive to use. Excellent support from the developer. Would recommend.

I think this is a very well designed app and very user friendly. I love the fact that I can email her a full report of my days, from supplements to medications to exercise to reactions but some times I have questions and symptoms unrelated to any of the categories and a notes category would make it 5 stars plus! EDIT: Please stop asking me to leave a review when I've already done so! So annoying grrrrr ...

Since the latest update the app quits randomly - super frustrating when in the middle of adding a recipe. Suggestion - when adding meals or creating a recipe, it would be great to be able to press multiple plus symbols next to your recent items without going back to prior page. Quick add?
replyContent: We're really sorry the app is intermittently closing on your device. Please contact our support to resolve the issue (More - Report an Issue). Re: multi-add can be done by tapping the multi-add button (the two green check marks to the right of the search bar). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Works great for my celiac needs to log food entry and bowel movements but wish it would allow blood sugar results too. It's hard to find an app that does both.
I cant rememeber my username as I got a new device but I can't find a way to find it?
replyContent: Please contact support at issues@skygazerlabs.com for assistance. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: I like the app. It helps me keep track of many things. I do wish the barcode database outside the US was bigger. I don't really want to take the time to enter all the ingredients. Sleep quality is my problem button. I want to know exactly how long I sleep. Even if I enter start time when I go to sleep, it automatically defaults to 8 hours before my wake up time when I enter end sleep time. So I do not have an accurate measure of sleep time. Unless I write down the time I go to sleep.
I have forgotten my login ID and password. Please let me know how to retrieve that
replyContent: Please email our support team at: support@mysymptoms.net and we'll provide assistance. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Easy to use.
Very helpful app

Good app for entering your data (what you eat, how much and when), but the Analysis algorithm needs some work!! Not easy to comprehend, and I dont think I have problems with sweet potatoes, despite what it says.

This app somehow resonates with me. I have NEVER been able to keep a journal despite countless tries. I use this for everything. The timeline scroll works for me better than any app I have ever tried!! I use the notes line for journaling..I scroll and everything is there!! Bravo!!!!

The diary of symptoms is chronological. I was hoping to use to show my doctor but he wouldn't have time the way it's set up. You can't copy routines, medications, foods from one day to the next. If I take something every day, should be a date range option. It is somewhat useful, but not being able to out your daily meds or supplements in a date range makes it too time-consuming. I use the app to keep track of symptoms for a disability claim.
replyContent: We're sorry you are unhappy with the app. mySymptoms provide a PDF report of your diary that you can share with your clinician. The analysis results aren't included in the PDF, and are only in the app. Whole events can be copied from day to day - simply tap on an event and tap the copy button. We hope this helps. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: I have crohn's - this is an excellent app for logging symptoms.
Really useful
This app allows me to easily keep track and chart symptoms in the middle of a hectic lifestyle.

I love this app. You can create any symptoms you want to track, all the food and medication databases have tons of pre-populated options to pick from. Intuitive and easy to use. It's been a great help on determining what has been causing which symptoms.
replyContent: Thanks for your review! We're glad to hear you love mySymptoms and that it's helping. If you have any feedback to help us improve the app, please contact us either in the app (More > Suggestions) or by email: hello@mysymptoms.net. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Works good, does everything I need. Would love to see dark mode support. It's hard on eyes at 3 am.

So there were a number of issues with this app, making me regret spending $6 on it. Incomplete Food Database: I tried scanning three different kinds of coffee and 4 different kinds of breakfast cereal and none of them produced a result. I can only conclude that this is either an incomplete implementation of a database, or just meant to add a UPC code while still having to add every food by hand. This would defeat the purpose of having a bar code scanner in the first the place. Medication Data: Also incomplete. Two common medications showed as not being in the database. It defeats the purpose of having a database with bar codes if I have to enter in the data myself. I downloaded the app because of the databases. It makes me regret not having tested this feature more extensively before buying the paid version. Incomplete UI: Check marks for data entry sometimes layer over each other, sometimes right next to each other. The UI looks unfinished. There's no underlying design to it and it looks rushed. I don't mean to pile it on, so I'll leave it here, but if you're going to charge $6 for an app that duplicates most functionality from apps like Cara which are free, it should look clean, well designed, and it should work well. The bar codes are pointless if everything has to be entered by hand anyway. It should also function well and be easy to read and look good on a flagship phone (Mine's a Samsung Note 9). I feel like I did not get my money's worth here, and would advise you to save your money on this incomplete, high priced application.
replyContent: We're very sorry the items you scanned didn't return a match. Our database varies by country, but has almost 500,000 items in the USA, and many 10,000's in other countries. However, not all items have barcodes recorded, and we're working on that - but a text search should work. Please contact support for a refund. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: It's fine, a bit too fiddly to do at the end of the day so I'm giving up to look elsewhere.
Like it!
Easy to track symptoms and to personalize food choices. A great way to see what you've been eating and taking.

Now you require registration?. Why would you link such personal matters to the internet. You are a dirty, creepy bunch. Was a decent app. Now youre just collecting peoples personal information. No one should download this app. Edit: if what you say is true, then it should be an option to the user, whether they wish to utilize your backup process. This should not be a requirement to use the app.
replyContent: We require registration so that you can sync your data between devices and have a secure backup. Accounts are anonymous, and we store your data in a secure database. We are not collecting any personal information. Please contact us at: issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can resolve this issue. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Paid for full version on the recommendation of my dietician so she and my GI doc can get a better handle on my food and symptoms. Used it dutifully for a few weeks to try to get the best data for them possible. Then got my period and realized this app doesn't have a way of tracking periods, making it utterly useless for almost 50% of adult users. Blargh. Wish I could get a refund. Wish there were apps that considered women when designing them.
replyContent: We're sorry there's currently no specific period tracking in the app - we plan to introduce it very soon. In the meantime, it's possible to add information under the 'Other' event type - many people use it for this purpose. If you are still unhappy, please contact our support at: issues@skygazerlabs.com. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Pretty good data base, but could use more entries.

Great app trying to figure out my issues. Lots of items to choose from and like you can add sleep quality, exercise, supplements, etc. Sometimes have a bit of trouble remembering to add my data. Had a bit of trouble figuring out how to add a recipe vs one ingredient for what I ate...took some time to play with it. Occasionally still can't figure out where my ingredient just disappeared to, but easy to start over again. All in all, I'm glad I'm using this app!
So far this app is doing what I need. It can track basically everything, you can pre enter or back enter and there are tons of options. Worth it.
The UI is a bit clunky but otherwise it's pretty powerful and customisable.

Incredible app for tracking my UC. Let's me log everything I want, and keep track of how things like diet affect my symptoms. Has been a massive help since starting the specific carbohydrate diet However, it would be helpful if it didn't go back to today when resuming the app. If I'm on another day, and I come back to the app, it resets to today.

New Device, Goodbye Access To App Data Got new phone and my user name and pass doesn't work. Thanks for nothing and for the loss of a year's Data. You gonna save the privacy world by storing sign in credentials on the device?? What good is that when you change devices, enter the correct info and you're locked out because the app won't recognize the sign in? No way to recover. Just idiotic.
replyContent: We're very sorry you are experiencing an issue logging in on a new device. This should work fine with your username (not your email address) and your password. Please contact our support so that we can help - issues@skygazerlabs.com. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Amazing way to keep track of every single aspect of my road to better health.

I think this app is great. It covers everything you need in order to track your food and body functions. The easy conversion of your tracked symptoms to PDF is great. My only concern is that the graphs and ratios given can be hard to interpret.
Works Fantastic :) really helps me

Excellent app so far. Well laid out and easy to use. The barcode reader is great and works REALLY well. Two improvements that could be made - 1. use different colours for different sections as it's easy to mix up "Item" with "Ingredients" or "A Kind Of" as they all look exactly the same. 2. go through the database and remove duplicate listings of ingredients and items so that only the most complete versions remain. Other than that, it's been very helpful indeed!

I was in the er and unable to tell doctors when I had taken medicine or what I had eaten for the last few days. I will now have that information thanks to this app. It is very easy to use and edit. Everyone should use this app.
so far so good... still early ..its easy to enter and add stuff.

The app was easy to use after the initial two or three days of learning how to use it. I do not have any type of IBS. I bought the app to track lectins and the various symptoms they caused me. After 3 months of diligently reporting all food, drink and supplements, this app was not useful to me in narrowing down which foods cause which symptoms.

this app could be fantastic. but there's a big problem. you can track outcomes like energy in relation to food. but all it will tell you is that there is a relationship between the food item and an energy level it won't tell you what energy level the food item tends to bring you to. this is a huge problem for me as it's the main reason I got the app. there needs to be a clear way to know if the food item is decreasing or increasing your energy.

it's a but cumbersome and I dont like that ur requires an extra step to search the community entries. but overall it's quite useful. what would make it better is to link to my Samsung Health and allowing me to upload photos of symptoms if they can be photographed.
very detailed and useful in helping me pin point food sensitivities. Takes a little initial work to get used to remembering to track everything in detail but well worth the effort.
Just started using it and i Love it already. Easy to use. Thank you.

The best health tracker I've found. Excellent customer support! Got a new phone and had trouble signing in (user error) and they got back to me right away and helped me get in. I'm confident they will help immediately if I have a real issue.
I live it
I am so grateful I found this app! It's been so helpful to be able to record exact foods, times, and symptoms.
Liking this app! once you've been making entries for awhile, it gets easy. You can add symptoms, too.

Absolutely the best app ever! I love this.. took only a day or two to really get used to it and now it is so easy. . You've thought of everything with this app it tracks what I eat, when I eat, medications I take, how I'm feeling, any pain I have, stress, you name it! Thank you so much to the people that built this.. Best money I ever spent...My Dr. will love this...
brilliant app.... excellent support.... tracks what I eat and the symptoms I need tracking
Absolutely love this!!! It is just what i have been searching for!
Thanks a lot great app.
Very easy to add foods, medication, etc
Flexible and simple.

replyContent: Thanks for your review. We're glad to hear you like mySymptoms. If you have any questions or feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: So far this app has been quite useful in terms of keeping a food diary, and tracking symptoms. I've yet to see how helpful the statistical analysis is correlating food to symptoms. As a food diary, it's database is not very populated, and entry can get a bit tedious. Not present in this app that I'd like to see: 1) the ability to track not just symptoms, but positive outcomes as well, and 2) the ability to tag foods, so all foods that fall into an allergy category can be identified.
replyContent: Thanks for your review and feedback. When searching the database, please enter the first few characters of the name and then tap the 'search for: (name)' option at bottom of the search results - this searches our cloud database. Positive(!) symptoms can be added and tracked/analyzed. Tags - noted. Thanks! Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: i love love love this app
I find it to be a very practical App. It has helped me so much.
Excellent way to track food intake and symptoms. It is easy to use.

This app is my new "go-to" app for tracking and analyzing what types of foods negatively *AND* positively affect my overall health!! I'd like to see if there's a chance that the dev'ers would consider adding a local DB backup-and-export/import feature? It would enable the user to "pick up right where they left off" when they have to switch devices. If that can be added, I'd give it 6 stars...
replyContent: Thanks for your review! When moving devices please take note of your username (see More - User Settings) and password, then simply login with the same username and password on your new device. mySymptoms will then sync all your data to the new device (this can take time depending on how much data). We hope this helps. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content:
Track everything in and everything out. No counting calories, just tracking 
food and meds and symptoms. Look for connections between symptoms, their 
severity, and foods or medications/supplements that you take. Set reminders 
for logging meals and regular meds. Good focus on privacy and still allows 
community-built food database so you don't have to create recipes for every 
single thing. Highly recommend.
replyContent: Thanks for your review. If you have any questions or feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content:
Really helpful app for tracking your meals and symptoms. PROS: relatively 
simple to use the basic features, allows tracking of lots of different 
things (BMs, stress, environment, food, etc.), and you can export your data 
to PDF or excel in order to give it to your GI/dietician. Lots of 
customizable options to add brands, serving sizes, etc CONS: adding recipes 
with lots of ingredients is tedious, which means I usually take shortcuts 
and therefore don't get much out of the analysis options. I haven't had any 
luck so far with the barcode scanner. WISHLIST: I wish there was a button 
to indicate if you are out for a particular meal, and I wish that you could 
import recipes from the web (similar to the Paprika app). It would also be 
nice if you could add photos to your log, so if you don't have time to log 
a meal, you could take a picture as a reminder of what you ate.
replyContent: Thanks for your review and constructive feedback - we're listening and consider all suggestions. If you have any questions or additional feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content:
Took me a bit to get used to it and figure out all the shortcuts but once 
you've got it set up with your faves, works very well. Even has reminders! 
Be sure to read the tutorials. It's important to understand how the stats 
work.
replyContent: Thanks for your review. If you have any questions or feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content:
I used this on and off for years. Decided I needed to start tracking again, 
opened the app, and it requires an account. I really liked this app... It 
was important to me that my data was stored locally and that I could create 
my own backups. It's now just a useless app on my phone wasting space, 
though it's hard to delete since I paid for it.
replyContent: Hi. Old accounts still provide the option to store your data on the device only. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can provide assistance. Also worth noting that our cloud based accounts are secure and anonymous to protect your privacy. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Wonderful. A great app.
replyContent: Thanks for your review. If you have any questions or feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

replyContent: Thanks for your review. If you have any questions or feedback, please feel free to contact us (hello@mysymptoms.net). Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Simple, easy to use. Made it easy to follow my condition

has been very handy for recording food and symptoms. not everything i eat 
is in the database but it's easy to add them. haven't figured out how to 
get helpful data from the analysis yet, i probably need to continue adding 
data to improve its accuracy. developers take privacy seriously with this 
data.
Really great for tracking foods, stress, symptoms and many other things.

This is a great base app for figuring out your dietary needs and tracking 
your different digestive habits. The biggest downside is that the food 
database system set in place is entirely reliant on users submitting their 
own food entries, and there aren't enough users currently to support that 
kind of system.
Fantastic for tracking food sensitives.

It's really tough to add new foods. There's a big plus at the bottom, but 
that doesn't do it. But if you press the tick that ALSO doesn't seem to do 
it and also puts you back at the logging screen without your new entry 
added. It's even more confusing when trying to add a 'type of' at the same 
time. Probably it's user error, but it isn't great that I apparently need 
to find the manual to understand how to work the user interface. It's a 
shame it isn't consistent with current UI Android guidelines.
replyContent: Hi. To add a new event to the diary please tap the big plus button. To add a food to an event, tap the 'Add...' option under contents, then search for a food and tap + next to the food to add it to the event. Once you've finished adding foods to the event, tap the check mark / tick to save the event. We hope this helps.

content:
For tracking what you consume and how you feel it is invaluable. I could 
not imagine trying to do an elimination diet without it. I tried to create 
a spreadsheet for it and gave up. This app made it possible to get the most 
data out of the reintroduction phase.

Outstanding app. The best available for charting and analyzing symptoms. 
Allows for customization. Easy to use.

Excellent, quick response from customer support. The app is helpful except 
that the analysis charts need improvement. No matter what onset delay I 
select, Its algorithm makes hundreds of foods show up, and doesn't easily 
help rule things out. Also people have added thousands of items improperly 
to the food database, creating tons of clutter and not linking equivalent 
ingredients. Don't stupidly add "handful of strawberries" or "diced 
potatoes" or "1/2 cup tomato sauce". Just enter the ingredient!

This is the first review I've written for an app. It's the perfect tool for 
tracking and it has a very simple and nice interface. Also, easy to share 
data with my Functional Nutritionist. Thanks for this great app.

The reason why this harsh rating is now you need a account. First it was offline and locally. The reason why I bought the app is now gone. So now I hope for a update or refund. It used to work fine.  Edit: thanks for the reply, switched phones so missed the no account option. The app lost its value for me. Keep it up
replyContent: Upgrading a pre-cloud account version of the app asks if you wish to skip the cloud account. If you missed it, sync can still be turned off by going to More - User Settings. Any new installs require a cloud account, enabling us to offer new services in future. Please contact us (More - Report an Issue) for further assistance. mySymptoms team

content: This app helps to identify substances  that cause unpleasant symptoms. Of course the quality of the report depends on input accuracy and completion. Discomfort is motivating, I'm committed to the process. I highly recommend this tool if you to are suffering, or are simply curious. It's intuitive, I'm older, so technology may stump me in ways younger people would not be. I usually figure it out without too much time wasted. I'm working with a nutritionist, so I'm particularly pleased with sharing the diary. I prefer it to the hard copy diary she provided

Thanks for the app. All great and the only thing I find a bother is that you can't add titles (I would like to add mood etc.) so I just use 'other' to report mood. Also, just a suggestion - the ability to look back in time using a calendar type of page rather than having to slide back through the days individually. Thanks though, it's a great tool. ☺
replyContent: Thanks for your review. We plan to introduce mood events soon (like in our iOS app). We agree - a calendar review would be useful - we're certainly considering it along with a number of options. We hope you find the app useful! :-)

content: You can utilize this for extremely detailed information, or utilize it in a minimized fashion.  Very well done!
All I needed! Using it to help prevent psoriasis. Would recommend making graph with multiple symptoms, wider database of food/nutriment/drink and automatic weather input.
Entering everything you ate is a bit of a hassle, but really gave me some insight
I like the app. It is helping me find food triggers which is why I downloaded it. I'm using it in conjunction with The Elimination Diet and it is helping.
2 days in I found a allergic reaction because I was tracking my food, drinks and medications! Love this app!
I like the app. I'm using it more for a food diary.  I would like to be able to add pictures in the notes section.  I could take pictures of what I'm eating and or the labels.
Great features for tracking diet and symptoms. It takes dicipline to enter everything you eat and any symptoms as they happen but the analysis makes it worthwhile.

Using to track my IBS symptoms. Selecting multiple ingredients at once is an appreciated update. Easy to make my own recipe for what I eat often or copy meds from day to day to save steps. Wish there was a search feature for each day; like "When's the last time I ate that particular chicken dish?"
Tracking is a bit convoluted, and not quite sure how to use the data best, but it's helpful
Great app for tracking all kinds of food triggers and symptoms. Love that I can add a symptom specific to my child's health issues.

I agree with some other reviewers that while it has great functionality, it is just too time consuming to add ingredients. I've found it useful to add new foods and add their individual ingredients, but I keep putting off updating it because of the time it takes. The number of times I've started tracking and then stopping after a few days are innumerable. I would suggest to simplify it somewhat and make it more user friendly. The look and feel of the app is also not very appealing, which for me makes a huge difference. There are just too many things to click on on one screen.
Takes several steps to add even one entry which makes it very time consuming to keep a record.

It seemed like a great app but it just tries to do too much. Adding ingredients one by one is time consuming as you have to set portions separately and the portion size setting vary too much. It's 8:30pm and I'm still trying to add my lunch. I was really hopeful that I'd be able to track my symptoms during my IBS treatment but I guess its back to the drawing board for me.
replyContent: Hi. When searching for foods, please ensure you search our online food database - it includes many foods with ingredients. Also - portions / quantities is optional - it's there if you want to use it, but is not required. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: This is really helpful. And the fact that my doctor can download it, means a lot.
Bought the full app, get to registration and it tells me it is not licensed and to purchase it from the app store?
replyContent:
We're sorry you're experiencing a problem. Please try powering down your device and then turn it back on again - this refreshes everything and should hopefully fix the issue.  

If you continue to experience problems after doing this, please let us know by going to More > Report an Issue.

Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: I really like the idea of this app, but I just can't keep up with it.  It takes me to long to input the information so I end up hitting a few events and missing a few, then dropping it altogether.  I use an app called "mighty grocery" that manages grocery shopping lists.  One of the things that I really like about it is that I can add entries via voice.  You can say "a gallon of milk and one box of golden grams and apples and aspirin and toilet paper and 2 pizzas and ketchup".  The result would add 6 line items with one simple voice command.  Imagine saying, "a cheeseburger and french fries and coke and a chocolate chip cookie"  and DONE.... would be nice.
I love this app! It helps me and my physicians with monitoring my health indicators.
Very very useful. Would be improved if you could more quickly select multiple items on a list. Edit: thanks to the app team for the response, turns out you can!
replyContent: Thanks for your review. To select multiple items from the food search, please tap the check mark in the green circle to the right of the search bar. This toggles on/off for multi-select. We hope this helps. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: I am obsessed with this app. As a holistic nutritionist and health coach I know it's super important to keep track of what we eat and I have been looking for something to help me keep track of my health concerns, my sleep and my food and supplements as they vary and this has been so helpful. I love how I can create or find foods or supplements with lots of ingredients. I had both my daughters get the app too so we can share correct information with their doctors. It's awesome! Everyone needs this app.

Great app for tracking all kinds of exposures and symptoms. Not as much available food data as other apps I've used (barcodes rarely find a match), but allows the user to add those details and saves it for later use. Its helping me be aware of exposures and results even before I have enough data over time to find meaningful correlations (my symptoms are subtler than others' will be).
Great app and very responsive developers.  I had a problem and they immediately took care of it.  Thanks, devs.
replyContent:
Glad to help. Sorry for the inconvenience caused. Thanks also for updating your review. 

If you experience any further issues, or have any feedback, please contact us at: issues@skygazerlabs.com

Kind regards, 

mySymptoms team

content: I like the app really much - I'm just missing the ability to add multiple types of bowel movements at once
Works great for recording symptoms, bowel movement, sleep quality and diet. I printed out the last 30 days and gave it to my doctor, he was so excited. I feel it improved the time spent with him.
Great way to track. My doc will appreciate info as we aearch for diagnosis. Found that my headaches are more often than I thought.

Considering about 90% of regular human food punches through my digestive tract with impunity, it's extremely important for me to keep track of what goes into me and what it does. The fact that this app also allows for ingredients lists is fantastic, as most of the food I eat is custom made by my wife.

I use my husband's emaik.  I have a lot of health problems. Gatroperisis spasmodic dysphonia gerd dysphagia achalasia ibs dumping snydrome to name a few....I found this a few years ago and it is so valuable to me and my doctor's!  If you have any health issues please try this! I always have it with me and can easily adjust to my needs!

Have been using for about 5 days. Although not designed for blood pressure tracking, I am using it for that, and it is a Godsend. The ability to simply log "what" I eat, and not "how much" or calories is ideal. If I want more details, I can add them via Notes. Already I am seeing trends in BP related to foods and other factors I am tracking.  Will be glad to beta-test any BP functionality which may be added. Thanks for this fantastic tool for health!
Great app, would be fantastic if you had a system to input  the data using a computer, either window/Mac support or just a website where you log  in to input the data with pc as well.
One of the best built apps I've used. It does what it claims and it does it well. Highly recommend.
Does everything I am after and more.
Nice app, good tech support, wish it synced with S health or other activity trackers
It seems the newer version solved most of the problems.
replyContent: That's great. Thank you. :-) Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Fantastic app for tracking cause and effect of diet, meds, etc.
Best app for monitoring food, stress suppliments. Have not seen anything like it. It loses a star because i have yet to scan an item that is in the food database.
Love being able to customize symptoms.  I highly recommend this app.  Support is excellent.  Very quick and responsive.

Helped me find a number of food allergies that had been plaguing me for a long while.  Generally, an excellent program made far more useful with the addition of cloud sync. Loses one star for the general wonkiness of inputting food items, but otherwise an excellent program.

Been using this to track my IBS for several years and it's a real boon. Recent update added cloud sync and backup which I'm sure will be great for some people but why did we have to loose the old stand alone backup? I like to have my data under my control and don't need cloud sync so PLEASE, restore the old backup method as well (surely we can have both can't we?).
replyContent: Hi Mark, thanks for your review. We will take a look at the technicalities of providing the backup option again for non-sync'ing accounts. I think we can. Keep an eye out for the updates. Kind regards, mySymptoms team. Update: This will be included in the next update.

content: Update lost all my data
How do you ensure that all if your previously entered records get transferred to my new Samsung Galaxy Note 8 phone?
replyContent: Hi. There's a backup option under the More tab - please use it to email yourself a backup, then open it on your new device and tap on the attachment and choose to open it with mySymptoms, then follow the prompts. If you require further assistance, please contact us from the More tab, Report an Issue. Kind regard, mySymptoms team.

content: Really like this app, but doesn't allow you to track glucose, BP, or heart rate

So helpful. Easy to use once you get the hang of it. Possibly more time consuming than writing it down manually, but it correlates the results for you, making it easier in the long run. Only annoying thing is when I enter a glass of water after a meal, the app thinks the water is causing the problem.

Nimble to navigate thro, adaptable to your personal needs, covers all the factors you might want to record.  Im looking forward to having enough data to see the correlations between foods and symptoms.
Once you get the hang of entering foods and recipes, it gets quite easy. A great way to record your daily food and health habits.

Long time user of this app. Extremely useful for tracking your diet , medication etc. The suspect food reports are good but frankly I don't tend to use them much. I know what's likely to cause me trouble. Can be used as a stand alone drug tracker to monitor doses. The interface can be a challenge at first but it's grown on me enormously. UPDATE Aug 2017 - sync ability now up and running! Great news.
Okay. The way my brain works just doesn't jive really with the reporting. I'm looking for more obvious possible triggers with less report customization.
Very useful, though the UI is a bit fiddly. I really like being able to track my food without having to see calorie count, which negatively affects my food choices.
Powerful and convenient.
Not perfect, but the best IBS tracker out there.

Great app, but I agree with another reviewer that often symptoms don't show up on the same say.  I'd also like to have it sync with other diet log trackers, like Spark People.  I have to enter my diet in two places.  Though other trackers don't always track ingredients details, just nutritional details needed for losing weight.  So the sync would also need to allow for input of ingredients (I'm thinking for processed foods, even the "healthy" ones).
Very helpful app to keep track of food and symptoms
It does a great job of capturing such a variety of data.
so far so good with keeping track of food, drink and symptoms. easy to learn and adjustment is minimal.
Nice app, would be nice if there was a web app to accompany it so one could do the input on a computer too.

It's very useful to keep track of things, easy to use. Wish there was a way to analyze results when symptoms are usually delayed, so like if symptoms show after about 3 days of consuming certain foods instead of immediate/same day. Overall highly recommended!

Its: concise but comprehensive enough; easily customisable;  and user friendly!  Therefore it has been very helpful in pinpointing possible root problems.  Not just diet related but exercise, sleep, stress etc which all play a part in health quality.  This is empowering.
Really wish the buttons on top right weren't so confusing. Could be more user friendly to be 5 stars.

I have used the application for months and am mostly happy with everything, but I would still like to address a couple of issues. For one, it can become difficult to navigate when adding an item that contains an item that contains an item etc... As silly as it may sound, the (sometimes long) process of looking up and inserting ingredients can make me forget which item I am currently working on. It would thus be much appreciated if there was a way to understand exactly which page you are on at all times. Secondly, it can be quite frustrating to lose some carefully inputted data when you accidentally click on the "Return" button while adding a number of ingredients to your new item (think muesli). Would it be possible to create a pop-up window that asks you to confirm whether you want to exit a given screen, whenever unsaved data would be lost in result? Many thanks in advance, and thank you for the application.
Good app for keeping track of what you eat.  However, I don't find the analysis function useful in helping me figure out my food triggers.
Great, just quite a lot of duplicates in the database e.g. 'egg' is in there many times!
It's good in theory. I wish that the database had more in it for tracking food allergies as that's my main goal for this. Pretty disappointing.
replyContent: Hi. Please could you email us at issues@skygazerlabs.com and explain what you would like to see in the app? We can then provide assistance and perhaps look at enhancements for the future. Thanks!

content: Works great. Good a keeping track of various different things for digestive issues
Amazing app! Has helped me so much!
Only started to us this app this week, so still learning and finding my way around this app. But if it does as it is "sold" it and fit for purpose I would be very happy, time will tell.
It never would open.
replyContent: Hi. Please try deleting the app from your device and re-installing. Please contact us at: issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can provide assistance.

content: I love this app! It makes it so easy to track my diet and symptoms. It's very flexible and so much more user friendly than other apps I've tried. I would highly recommend it!
Great help in tracking my GI symptoms.
I use it everyday it's a great app!!
Awesome app, very helpful. I'd just recommend automatic backups and it'd be nearly perfect.
Exactly what I needed, couldn't ask for a better app
The app beats having to keep a written diary ....it's easy and convenient to use for a contemporaneous record.
Takes a bit of getting used to but once you do and you have a list of your most common foods to choose from, it's great.

By nearly a month of deligent use, I'm let down.  If you inspect a previously entered recipe, the quantities reset to zero.  Boo!  When entering  "contents", such as food, into an "event", such as a meal, the quantity defaults to zero.  It will save 4 keystrokes for if the default is set to "1".     In general, the food quantities do not display when viewing your daily dairy, therefore most users tend to include the quantity into the food name, i.e. "carrot 1/2 cup" instead of naming the food "carrot".  This can result in "carrot" becoming two different food items if you ever enter a slightly different name.   I have many duplicates in my organizer.  There should be a way to combine duplicate items, although the only option is to delete item.    After 3 weeks of use, the analysis still seems inaccurate. There should be more information about the analysis and common mistakes users may make.  Skygazer labs has responded and offered to help.
replyContent: Hi. We're really sorry you're experiencing problems with the app. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can help. It sounds like there may be a problem related to the crashing on your device. Re: quantities - they are optional, so you don't need to set them to 1. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: Pretty simple and easy to use! I like how easy it is to input symptoms AND their intensity. I wish there were more foods in the database and it was quicker to add foods though.
Worth the money! Does what it says it says and have no technical problems.

I absolutely love this app & cannot "big' it up enough. I write down my entries everyday & after a certain length of time the app can help you work out certain food triggers & what most likely caused them & how long after eating it. I love being able to track everything I eat, drink & other stuff, I always used to forget! It's great how I can share all my notes with my Doctor too, she is able to analyse my diary & help me. I could write a lot more about this app, I really think it is fantastic!! :-)
I'm glad I can go back in and add details when I have more time.... Allows me to say drink or snack quickly and details afterward.

Best app. New updates make it even better. Would be great to have option to set default size/quantity to save time entering items. I'm still trying to figure out way to enter "template" recipe so I can re-use but adjust for the meal. Having nutrition data would be great.
Easy to use, great UI, wonderful analysis ❤ I use this daily and love it!
Starting an elimination diet to aid with ulcerative colitis. This app is thorough and easy to use.

I've been using this program for about a month. While I think it might be good for tracking some stuff. It is not easy to use, the help file is not that useful and the reports / graphs are limited. This being said,  I will keep trying. Will see.

I’ve tried 3 others tracking apps over the last 3 years, including MySymptoms. This year, I went back to MySymptoms. Surprise!! Enhancements over the last 3 years have taken it from good to great. It is more complex, and more difficult to use, but what software has more functionality without sacrificing usability? If it contained a nutritional database, it would be off the charts great! Check around… This is the best android app for correlating symptoms with conditions and was the first to identify my food sensitivities. I looked for better, but didn’t find it. It is well worth the cost, and I would pay more. Great development job! Need a beta tester or enhancement suggestions, put me on your list.
This app is great at what it does. It could be a little prettier, but functionally it's great :)

I find this app user friendly and intuitive. I like the scan barcode option. My only suggestion is to be able to print a report for only days a symptom was recorded. I'm supposed to be tracking everything I eat everyday for 2 months so printing out a report for 60 days is going to be excessively long, when my doctor only wants to see when I have symptoms.
Works very well... don't know why some people complain. It tracks my symptoms very well without any problem! This will make my doctors life much easier...
Super easy and lots of features. I hope the shared items continues to grow. It would be awesome if somehow it could help read the ingredients on labels. Not sure how easy that would be to implement.

I've used a few different apps for food tracking and this is my favorite. The one feature I would really love is the ability to search by food, so you could review your symptoms from the last time you ate a specific food. Also a better way to navigate through the calendar to view past days

I recommend this app because it helps me manage my IBS and GERD. The ease of this app has helped me to record and establish good eating habits that work for me. I have tried to keep track of my diet through pen and paper or using OneNote, but this app proved more convenient.
Takes a bit to learn to navigate but a good tracker. Haven't used long enough to see if analysis is helpful.

I purchased this to help with tracking the effects of diet on my ulcerative colitis.   I like how comprehensive it is and that it does contain some UK foods and has the option to add foods recipes and symptoms
replyContent: Hi. Thanks for your review. To add symptoms please go to Organizer - Symptoms and tap on the + button. I hope this helps.

content: This app is user friendly. If using the basics it is very quick to enter foods, etc. New items take a bit longer to enter, but once you do they are saved. Very useful to my doctor and I for seeing which foods may act as triggers as I can also document symptoms so easily. Great app!
Well built,  and great app

This has helped me ten fold in tracking things that trigger flare ups. What supplements or medications help! I love how I can track food, exercise, medications, and sleep all in one place... and then track my symptoms to correlate all together!!!
If it would have a way to track calories, carbs, protein, & fat it would be perfect

This app will be useful to me if I use it consistently and put in all the ingredients of each food I eat.  My character defect is I wait till latter part of the day and don't take the time to put in the ingredients.  The best thing is to doc as I do things so I don't get behind.  That way ill do it correctly.  I think this app is pretty close to perfect.  I only wish I could just scan the food and it would be in there & also provide a place to put how many calories are in the food bec I need a stop button.

This app is crucial for my health and helping me to identify what foods I am eating that are giving me hives. Very easy to use, and the copy feature is really helpful, as well as the bar code scanner to scan food labels in. Pretty impressed. Love the ability to email a PDF or .CSV file of the results to myself or someone else. These are critical features.
This was exactly what I was looking for.

I like this app, using it for my elimination diet. Couple of things: the swiping between days doesn't work, at all, which seems odd. Secondly, I'm tired of apps TELLING ME HOW TO LEAVE  A REVIEW. If I have any suggestions or complaints I will leave them wherever I please, STOP TELLING PEOPLE HOW TO COMPLAIN IN A WAY THAT MINIMISES DAMAGE FOR THE DEV. I can't be the only one getting sick of this.

Using this to combat a mystery illness until I get diagnosed. Can you add in moods to, because certain emotions can set off my immune system & I'd imagine it's the same for others to? The stress log is great, but need to be more specific about the type of stress like you can be with foods etc. Also as previously mentioned, some way of logging macronutrients clearly would be great. 4 stars, 5 if you make the improvements I'd like.

After using this app for a few days, i am now excited about entering everything in. So much better than my old paper diary. Some quirky things that take a little getting used to in terms of dirty entry - but that is minor compared to the benefits offered by the app.
Very customizable, includes meds, sleep, etc. Great for anyone tracking food & symptoms relationships, including people with FMS, CFS, ME, DM2, autoimmune & other chronic disorders.

This helped me identify foods that were causing me issues and I have been feeling much better.  I wish that it tracked nutrition too.  It would be interestng to at least be able to see how different levels of macronutrients might affect certain symptoms.

The format is clunky and not easy to navigate. It takes much longer than I would like to input all the info. It seems to have all of the pertinent info and great options for tracking and charts. Just needs some streamlining.
I develop applications for a living, and the user experience of this product is top notch!
I would only recommend to include menstruation duration as part of the entries

Using this app for 1 week. Very specific- tracks every ingredient, you can add recipes & save them as a favorite to reuse  later. Add symptoms you experience, track your energy levels and how well you are sleeping.  Everything is based on time and duration. Not so great-the Barcode scan feature doesnt have much preloaded so you have to manually add products anyway. Overall, very time consuming, hopefully will be worth it.
I'd be 5 stars if menstruation was an option to track. Perfect for elimination diets, finding allergies.

I'm updating my review because they just updated the app... This app has made it much easier to track meals and symptoms on the go as I try to identify trigger foods. They recently added the option to add quantities with the foods, which makes it much more useful. They also added a super-fast feature tour to point out easier ways to use the app so you don't have to muddle through. And you can download the data to analyze yourself.
I'm doing an elimination diet and this is a great tool in tracking down my reaction to food.

I've been trying to figure out which foods were making me sick. You can track what you eat & drink then how you feel afterwards. Within 2 days I figured out which food I had a sensitivity to and which foods I had complete intolerance to.
Very useful
This app does everything I need it to and more.  It logs everything I'm eating and all of my activities.  It has allowed me to see what triggers certain symptoms.  This app has been a lifesaver.

If anything this app is great for tracking input and output with symptoms.  it can easily exported to a PDF to bring to the doctors if needed.  you do have to track for a good amount of time to get enough symptoms to determine.the cause.  The app is only as good as you make it, as you need to be dedicated to inputting everything if you want it to be successful.
Serves as a food diary and a symptom tracker a consumption diary in general, highly recommended

Amazing app! Very helpful for tracking the foods that trigger issues. I've been able to pinpoint several foods that I'm sensitive to. Has a lot of details to add just to track any events or activities that effect you as well. Extremely beneficial!
The app works overall well. I tried many apps and this is the best. I only have some problem using then barcode scanner.
Tracts my food,  activities and symptoms easily!
Been using this for 6 months or so. Great to target problem foods, and the dev quickly responds to questions with help. Great job.
I like it better than some others I found.
Please add more outcome categories and ability to add symptoms from within diary.
replyContent: Hi. Thanks for your review. To add symptoms please go to Organizer - Symptoms and tap on the + button. I hope this helps.

content: For anyone who needs to track food, drink, medications, symptoms, or just wants to keep a keen eye on diet or medical issues this app is great. Been using for a couple of weeks now, easy and intuitive interface combined with quite a powerful data tracking app.  Definitely recommend!
I use it all the time. And when I've had trouble the developer has been quick to respond and listen to suggestions.
I have just started an elimination diet and this has been extremely helpful on documenting what is happening,  possible correlations and as a easy to use log.
a great app for following your food habits and symptoms.

The app works well and has a bunch of nice features, I just have to gripes. 1: the database needs to be improved, it is sorely lacking, and most items either need to be input manually, or there are a bunch of half complete entries that you can choose from. I think so far one item has successfully been input via the barcode scanner for me. 2: It's confusing, the diagnostics are confusing, there are a lot of categories (medicine and supplements are two different categories but definitely have some overlaps).
Great app does everything I need it to. No problems
Great app for trekking a diet
This app has one hell of a learning curve, but once you know how to use it, it's a great friend! I imagine I'll use it for years.

I have used this app for a couple of years. It has been very helpful. Under 'Other' I've included my activities, which helps me see how those have affected my emotional and physical health, stress levels and mood; not to mention  being a  journal of sorts. I just wish there was a calendar to click on , to return to a past date to review activities or issues without having to look at a saved file, or print it out. Even so, it's a great app!
Great app
As much as I despise having to keep a food and poop diary for my doctor, I'm happy that this app exists to make it just a little less painful.
Did they not bother to program in basic ingredients?  I'm having to add things like niacin and corn syrup...
replyContent: Hi. Sorry - we had a brief issue with our food database over the past 24 hrs. All fixed now!

content: Does exactly what I need it to
This app is very helpful for figuring out what triggers your symptoms.
I'm so thankful for this app; it's allowed me to manage my pain and energy levels much more efficiently, now that I can track the foods that affect me most.

Item entry can be confusing but the database is pretty through already. It can take several days to get enough days for the analysis to be interesting. Really needs multiple device sync and a weed interface.
Great app
Easy to use

My doctor told me to log everything I ate or drank and this app lets me even record the supplements he has me taking. The best part is I can run a report and email the pdf to an email to print and show my doctor each week. So far so good.
Really useful. The tick and plus ui is a bit more complicated than needed. Otherwise awesome.
Keep up the good work.
Very thorough once you get the hang of it.

I love that I can track body related issues and it lets you create your own symptoms, food, medications, etc. Helps so much to figure out patterns that cause unwanted symptoms. You can be as detailed as you want, it even has a place for notes for every entry.
Works well and easy to use!

Bar code scanner linking to specific items online and uploading the ingredients.  Or being able to paste a whole paragraph of ingredients from a product and the app takes all the recognizable ingredients and adds them in the product.

Syncs with drop box with no configuration. Simple and intuitive, easy to learn. Emails reports with statistics. Good enough for me. *Update 3/2016* Updated interface is clean and streamlined. Online database of foods is extensive and helpful. Backups are easy, and reports are interesting and useful. Great app, well worth the upgrade.
I have arthritis which is why I bought app.
replyContent: Hi. You can add symptoms in the Organizer under Symptoms - simply tap + on the menu. I hope this helps!

content: Please fix a bug where a new unsaved entry is lost if you switch to another app (or if screen goes blank).
replyContent: Hi. Sorry for the bug - we're fixing it and should have an update available in a few days time. UPDATE: This has now been fixed.

content: Extremely helpful! Highly recommend! Best app of its kind.
Better than other similar apps.
Hi this app appears to be useless.... Entries of foods eaten did not appear to save!  Also interface was not intuitive as it should be. Will be asking for refund.
replyContent: Hi. Please contact us at: issues@skygazerlabs.com so the we can help. Kind regards, mySymptoms team.

content: I have been struggling to feel better. Trying to figure out what works best. Being able to keep track of all the different pieces that help me feel good or feel bad has been amazing. Thank you for an app that helps me figure out what works for me!
Easy to use and very intuitive interface

By customizing the symptoms you can track almost any health condition along with medications taken,  environment,  stressors, foods, activity,  etc.  Would love to see a more robust upc code library and library of products with complete ingredient information is limited,  however,  each user can improve on this and add items you frequently consume.  Data analysis  is very useful.  Overall great app! !
This app's database is basically useless, it mostly relies on user input for information and the app is not what I thought it would be. Refund will be requested

Like folks say: It's the best I've found. But it's got a quirky logic, making for a #!!# learning curve. My suggestion: Save a bunch. Save when you add something. Save an event once you've added -anything- then save it again after you add something else. Save. Save. Add an ingredient? SAVE. Add another? SAVE. Go back and edit after you SAVE. Oh BY THE WAY don't save when you should hit ADD NEW ITEM, because hitting save then LOSES WHAT YOU'VE PUT IN! Also, only upgrade (to pay version) from inside the app.

There is a learning curve to this app,  but once you get the hang of it,  it's very easy to use.   It helps me track gastrointestinal issues and identify my food triggers.  I'm still learning the reporting function.

I find this app helpful. However, the input is clumsy and I frequently have to add ingredients multiple times. In one screen you add things one way, and in another screen another way. One wrong click and you have to start adding ingredients all over. I am very frustrated with that but otherwise like this app. I hope this issue gets resolved and then it'll be a 5 star app. UPDATE: Since most recent update all it does is crash when I try to run an analysis.

With my medical condition it is very important to keep track of diet & symptoms and this app makes it so much easier than writing everything down. This app is also far better than similar apps (I've tried a lot). The only thing I don't like is the medications portion of this app. But that's just personal preference.

This is a very thorough & intuitive app which I am using to find the cause of my dermatitis. Love that you can input a variety of potential causes that aren't just food & drink. Though I realise this is a food diary, it would be great if it could develop into a more general health app and have a 'products' category where I could add which products I am using on my skin & 'hormones' category for the lady's. I am currently using Environment for these. This is definitely the best app of its kind!
Getting better each update. Would be good if it could sync between devices.

This was a very useful tool in helping me better understand patterns and correlations between food and supplements and their effects on my health.  It's very flexible and intuitive and the ability to create an external html file was hugely beneficial in enabling me to send data to a third party.

This is app is very good in the way it uses statistics to compute trends. Having access to a cloud database is smart. Only problem is that it's a real chore to type in all the ingredients of a food product.

A good, fairly intuitive interface. Excellent ability to use, merge, or create your own items. Entering symptoms is troublesome because if you do it when they start how do you know the duration? Or if you wait then you are likely to forget. I'd like more transparency on how it comes to the conclusions it does.
But would like to be able to add symptoms. Also can be annoying to add individual items to a dish, but not have to meal save automatically.
replyContent: To add symptoms, go to the Organizer and tap on 'Symptoms', then tap + on the action bar to add a symptom. I hope this helps.

content: Pretty pleased with this app as it allows me to track my food as well as symptoms and bowel movement and vomiting. Only a few small changes for quality of app i would suggest is giving people the option to select size of stools as well as having the "notes" show on the main page so they are readable without having to open up each individual meal or movement. Great app though!
Easy enough to enter items, but had to create entries for most things as they were not in the database.

I'm not tech savvy so it was frustrating trying to figure out how to use the app with no instructions. Also, cant figure out the symptims screen. My symptoms aren't listed do I'm having to code my symptoms incorrectly. For example I use the ecsema scale to rate my abdominal cramps. However the app is helpful in tracking food intakevand patterns, do overall I continue to usevthe appbdaily.
Takes awhile to work out where everything but great reports
Really easy to use and easy to navigate; comes up with your previous entries and most things can be copied

This is a great tool go helping one find interactions, sensitivity, and the like. It has made a big improvement in my quality of life. The more detail the better. It does have a few bugs, all can be worked around. THE PAID VERSION IS WORTH IT!
This app is exactly what I've been looking for. It works very well, and has tons of functionality. The dev is friendly, and quick to respond questions and concerns. Well done.
I'm still learning the app, but it's been really useful so far.

I have gastroparesis  (GP) and this is a great tool to track symptoms, food, exercise, stress and more. I can then export to show my doctors. More importantly, I can look for trends as to what sets off a nasty flare up and what helps.
Cloud search is useless and it often fails to save. Analysis useless unless you can break down recipes!
Only issue is i eat the same things too often so hard to find corelations!
I can add specific symptoms. I would like to see food choices on the main page rather than generic meal titles
I love this app. Once you get the hang of it, it's really easy to put in your food and symptoms.

I can't just search and find the names of some lone herbs.  I'm allergic to the lamiaceae plant family. so mint, nettle, lavender, fennel, etc.   Its kind of hard to add everything by hand when I'm allergic to over 50 plants and have the near same reaction with all of them. And need to watch my symptoms for when something says "ingredients; spices"
replyContent: Hi. Any item can be added to the app. Simply tap + on the search screen if you can't find what you're looking for. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com if you require further support.

content: I love being able to add my own symptoms and how it saves my favourite foods

It works well for tracking symptoms, but the reports aren't always easy to read, you have to really figure out what each one is telling you. Also, would be nice if they added nutritional information for the database, if you are tracking symptoms and weight, entering everything you do twice is a little unrealistic.  Plus, with the reports and algorithms possible in the app already, you could really do an in depth analysis of your dietary needs.
I was hoping to use this app to track my IC symptoms, but it doesn't have any options for bladder pain, urination... UPDATE figured out how to put my own symptoms, now this app is really useful
replyContent: Hi. To add your own symptoms go to Organizer > Symptoms and tap Tap on + on the action bar, then enter the name of the new symptom and tap the check / tick on the action bar. I hope this helps.

content: App to track all symptoms,  food,  digestive functions, energy, sleep and more. Not only can you use it as a diary, you can track what food or event may cause your symptoms. Very cool. Mostly user friendly.

Before finding this app, I was using 3 separated apps to monitor my issues. Now, this one has everything! The ease of inputting the data is not another headache to deal with. When I am able to link it to my Fitbit, I will give it a 5! I love it!!!
So far so good. Bought this hoping the algorithm can help me figure out the root cause of my troubles. Either way, logging your eating is an important habit to solving IBS.

Really easy to use and track just about everything. My only complaint is the food database seems to be lacking a lot and requires you to manually add a lot. I have also never found a barcode that successfully scans. It would also be nice if it would integrate with other calorie trackers so I don't need to double entry.

Need to be able to add amount of food or drink. Need to be able to add daily medication as well. Also where do I see the list of medications I have added in the organizer? Bar code scanner works fine on my Galaxy S5. Also having to click the add button twice for an entry is a bit annoying unless I'm doing it wrong. Also the items themselves. Black tea. White(with milk) Sugar? Amount? This is what I mean.
Great app!
Everything in one spot with the option to celebrate reports and back up data. So far so good!
I enjoy using this app. Its a great way to keep track of what I consume each day, what time its consumed, and any side effects. Great app
Exactly what I needed. Makes keeping a food diary easy. Huge community backed database of food etc.
Allows me to keep track and email my reports to my Nutritionist and doctor
Upon installing and opening the app, It's telling me to purchase the app as it's not licensed! Uninstalled and reinstalled it over and over again no luck!
replyContent: Hi. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can assist.

content: I have been using this app for a little over three months.  It has been useful to figure out what some of the triggers are. I like that I can add in different symptoms. The one thing I do forget and I'm not sure of its possible to fix/add is that I have to remind myself to add in the duration of the symptoms which I sometimes don't get around to do. But otherwise I recommend this app and encourage users to share their ingredients,  it makes it so much easier to input data!

Intuitive interface. Easy and fairly quick to add food entries. Adding and building up a list of my commonly used foods and meds has taken some time. Hopefully as this app gains popularity in my country the barcode scan function will become more relevant as others add more store bought products.
Dificult to enter data or add new items

It was a little tricky at first, trying to figure out how to enter new items.  But, after I got the hang of it, I just edit away.  This is an excellent app for keeping track of symptoms and how they might be affected by food and other factors (e.g., barometric pressure is one I added).  Just having to think about it and record things has made me more aware of correlations than ever before.  This came at just the right time.

This app desperately needs an option for adding portion sizes (in g and ml, please) as with some food intolerances like fructose or histamin symptoms depend on the overall amount consumed. Otherwise lots of potential, but the app seems more or less abandoned...
replyContent: Hi. Thanks for your feedback - we plan to introduce portion sizes in a future update. A new update is due shortly.

content: Works well.  Five stars if you fix the glitch where changing am to pm makes the date of the event skip back or forward a calendar day.

This app makes it very simple and fat to track diet, potential trigger foods, symptoms, energy levels, and even exercise throughout each day. I took a star of because I was looking forward to a useful correlation component, but that part still has a ways to go.
Excellent way to track food and symptoms
Since being diagnosed with UC I have struggled to keep note of everything in my life. This really helps you to do that with little effort, making it easier for yourself and doctors helping you.
Really helped me manage my food and symptoms
Good for finding what ails you
Very easy to use. Stores lots of detail

The CSV report didn't have notes but the HTML would have been great if the formatting wasn't awkward. I wish it could keep the notes spaced the way they are in the app. They all run together and then there are a lot of unnecessary characters that show under the date, next to the time.
Need a better way to document symptoms. It asks for the end time not the start time.
replyContent: Hi. The start time of a symptom is the time of the event at the top of the screen. The end time is optional. I hope this helps.

content: The most useful app that I have.

I tried a few other food diary apps before this and this one is definitely the best. The database of foods is pretty small but entering manually is fine. It's very thorough which is good! And I haven't used it yet but the export for doctor function looks like it could be great.
Works great for what it is designed to do. Could not ask for anything better. And the reports are nice for the doctor.
You can add as much or as little detail as you want on ingredients, symptoms, medications, and activities. Graphs are helpful. Even my GI doctor is impressed at how well I can track my symptoms.

Ok this is my 2nd review. I figured out thanks to CS how to run a report without deleting all entries, I  probably should have read the instructions before:-) Still hoping for sync with fitbit they say it's  in the works.   I must say I  still haven't really figured out how to understand the report in my case there is lots of data.  This is a brilliant app and something beneficial for people with chronic illness. I would like to see the sleep record time intervals instead of just start and end.

I really like how I can track all symptoms that I have and also customize them. It is also very easy to input food and create my own recipes. What I would like is the ability to put in the amount of food or supplements taken.

I have just started using this app and finding it quite convenient at this early stage.  However at this early stage i think there is one aspect missing which really could help improve its usefulness. When selecting food/drink intake it would be good to also be able to track intake amount as a separate function to item selection.  Allow us to track food number, weight, litre, and/or more arbitrary quantities (Plate/cup/can/bottle/ + half etc) would be useful when using it as a general consumption diary.  I hope through future updates eventually it could be expanded out to a calorie food calculator to use inconjunction with it exercise tracker.
Best way to track your intake
I just wish you could customize symptoms. I.e I am looking to track different types of abdominal pain, separate from generic stomach pain
replyContent: Hi. You can add your own symptoms by going to Organizer and then Symptoms and then tap the + button. I hope this helps.

content: Haven't found another app that has the same capacity to analyse correlations between foods and reactions. Few small issues: barcode reader is frequently inaccurate; database of foods currently small (will grow with more users); no ability to add amount of food; some important symptoms and events missing from options. Look forward to continued development of this app.
Easy and quick to use for keeping a record of what you eat and related things. Everything i needed.
It too a bit of time to learn how to use but well worth it!
Very useful.  Fairly easy to use.  No glitches so far.

Previously rated 2* cause I thought I couldn't add more symptoms.  On redownload I found the user manual that explained how to do it.  Not very intuitive but it works. No links with My Fitness Pal though which is a pity

Like a lot for ease of tracking and recording all my medical notes - i actually don't use the symptom algorithm at all; but the format is great for logging taking medication, my disease symptoms, etc - which I can easily download to share with my doctor or track my health.  I'd mark it 5 stars if it was better designed for that use,  but I just create any categories i need in the "others" area
Great
Tried to load food and it has very little in it's library.  It won't search the web and it won't log all the food.  Very difficult to navigate.
replyContent: Hi Dianne. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can help.

content: Amazing. A must-have app for anyone suffering with digestive discomfort and want to get it sorted. The developer is also quick to comment on anything you may wish to ask / remark. I am really pleased I bought this.
replyContent: Hi. You can add your own symptoms by going to Organizer > Symptoms and then tap the + button. I hope this helps.

content: Exactly what I was looking for! Very impressed and Is worth twice the price. Ability to add your own symptoms is one of the many great features.  Thank you Dev!
I have been using this application for a while now, it has improved a lot from previous versions and software support has been good.

Items easy to record. New items build your list so the app evolves with you & gets easier to use with each entry. The scanning function is pretty useless - I am based in Poland so I assume products for this region not yet in app DB. Look forward to getting to know the app more with increased usage. The support is excellent - receptive to feedback, courteous & timely.

A bit tedious getting started entering foods, but it does get much easier with time. Takes a few too many clicks though, when adding new things. I like the categories a lot. I just wish the Results tab was easier to understand. I have read the user guide a few times and am still not quite sure what I'm looking at or how to use that information. I would also suggest adding a way to include portion size. That can really make a difference when it comes to food sensitivity.  I am enjoying this app though. It's far more helpful than any of the others I've tried so far. Looking forward to sharing the results with my nutritionist at our next appointment in a few weeks! :)
Beautifully designed, simple to use and extremely intuitive. I have only just started to use this application, but can already see the potential improvements it will make to my lifestyle.
Easy to use, add or remove stuff, great for following a medical diet n meds taken, symptoms too.
Does not have a comprehensive food database.  Scan Barcode does not recognize foods either.
It would be better if I could take a photo of the ingredients and nutritional label to link to the food, as I need to forward this to my doctor.

I'm a picky SOB and this app impressed me.   The biggest way they could improve this app is to enhance functionality for people who don't have their phones with them all the time. If they were to offer an online way of updating your database that could be used across platforms, it would help tremendously. Also, inputting times of meals, exercise, symptoms etc retroactivly is a hassle. They need a better method to do that.  Otherwise, it's a great, functional way to keep track of your daily food intake.

This app has improved loads since I last used it about a year ago. Well done for the improvements.  Adding your own recipes can get a bit confusing sometimes as the screens for adding a meal, a recipe and the ingredients all look the same and it's difficult to tell which 'level' you are at. Also outputting reports in pdf would be very useful. But overall very good.
Very helpful

Great tool! Is there a way to connect foods: e.g. taco and tortilla chips should be connected, because both contain corn flower. Now when I analyze the symptoms they are listed as completely different items, but they actually correlate. Thanks!
Since my daughter and I both have health issues need tracking I wish there was a option to have more than one user on a device

This is generally a good app, would be better if you could copy a food from one day to the next as I eat the same for breakfast most days and that you could move foods between groups e.g. lunch to dinner. I have yet to find any major problems with it.
replyContent: Hi Helen. Thanks for your review. To copy a meal from one day to the next, open the existing meal event, scroll to the bottom and tap on the copy button - this will create a copy with the date/time set to the current date/time. Modify as required and then tap the check/tick button. I hope this helps.

content: Great to track diet, exercise,  symptoms and life!

Would 5 star after some bugs are fixed. Worth the money. Best app I could find. Great way to backup and format diary for doctors. App should not be full screen. Is the back end database synced with iPhone users? Missing some common items (m&ms). When making complicated items I save my progress often cause I am afraid of losing items. Too easy to exit the entry of a complicated item. Barcode scanner is really inaccurate and therefore useless.

Brilliant, simple app for logging what you eat, symptoms, bowel movements etc. Has a useful backup option that I recently used to transfer to a new phone. Generates an HTML report of food dairy that you can email directly from the app to your nutritionist or Dietician. It usefully stores recipes and you can chose to add products to the shared database. Worth the small list price! Not a large list of products currently in the database, but this will increase as users add more.

Once you set up your "favorites" this app is an excellent way to track diet, exercise, symptoms, medications, etc. I also love that you can export your data to a pdf or an html file (html is cleaner and more organized). Though it seems to be geared more toward stomach problems, you can add any other symptoms in the "other" category, which is what I did. Also to note, I don't use the shared options for the app.
Great for tracking my IBS symptoms!
The app won't use my wifi to verify this subscription so the app won't open. I'm in a location where I can't get data unless through wifi. The app is useless to me at this point.

I DL the app yesterday and support for this app is amazing! I've had two questions & the developer got back to me incredibly fast! The amount of foods aren't as varied as MFP BUUUT keep in mind as more ppl share the food they're eating the larger the database will be.

Seems quite good so far.  Improvements I'd recommend could include an ability to sync between devices and do auto-backup (using Dropbox for example). Also an ability to add in basic volumes would be good.
It's good. Problem is the shared good database isn't populated well, I.e., scanning barcodes turns up no items. More users need to participate in this.
Potentially very good app with one glaring omission which spoils it. There appears to be no password protection for your personal data! Would be 5 stars if added.

This is a useful basic app for tracking what you eat versus how you feel.  Problems: It does crash on occasion (Android 5.x Nexus 7) and it seems to do so more often when the app is brought from background to foreground.
