This seems to be avoidable if you always close out of the app.  Need improvement: 1)Symptoms. Seeing as how you could register anything else, I was surprised to see a fixed listed of symptoms (only 9!) and it doesn't even include constipation for instance, a very common food related symptom that accompanies many conditions. They really need to make symptoms editable!  2) Cache food ingredients that are frequently used! Once convenience is that dishes and drinks that you consume regularly are remembered in a seperate tab for easy adding. However, if you are like me and 1. have a strict diet to follow and 2. can't eat out and don't cook according to recipes, then every time I cook, I use a slightly different combination of the same ingredients. Unfortunately, when adding ingredients to a dish, a process identical to adding a drink or dish to a meal, they don't have a list of frequently used ingredients. I only have a list of 20 I use, but I type in every meal...:(
replyContent: Hi Chris. To add your own symptoms go to Organizer > Symptoms and then tap the + button. Re: crashes, please could you ensure you submit the crash reports when prompted, we will then fix any bugs. Re: favorites for recipes - good idea - it's been added to our task list for a future update. Thanks!

content: Easy way to keep track. Love it!

I love this app.  It is very usefull.  In terms of improvement, it would be nice if you would turn this into a full cloud app.  It would be nice to log info from my mobile device as well as my pc.  A supporting web app would also be very usefull.  Thanks
Only trouble when I tried to print it off.  I couldn't choose just a week.  It printed the whole 3 months.
replyContent: Hi. On the report screen, you should have the option to select 1 week, 1 month, all, or set a date range. Simply tap on one to select it. If you continue to experience problems, please email us at issues@skygazerlabs.com so that we can help.

content: To try and tackle the subject of dietary issues must be extremily difficult. Not many developers are brave enough to take this on. Sure you might find areas that are not quite what you want but for this subject you never will. If for no other reason this app enables you to create any excellent and comprehensive record of your diet to help a dietitian. There is so much more but people must make the effort of entering info. I have nothing but praise for this very helpful developer.

I love everything about this app. I've been trying to pinpoint what causes particular symptoms and when and this is really helping. It's also handy because I now have all of the information available in one place and will be able to show this to my doctor.
The app is doing what it promises. The developer is honest and provides instant support.

I suffer from strange allergic type reactions. Thought this app would be perfect to find my triggers -well they make you choose from the symptoms they think you would have. Allergies and other mast cell disease triggers have way way more symptoms than these.To be called my symptoms, when they don't let you enter YOUR SYMPTOMS is misleading. Update - OK I can add my own symptoms which is great, but only three stars because this should be more obvious. The interface needs work. I'll keep using it.
replyContent: You can add any of your own symptoms by going to the Organizer, tap on Symptoms and then the add button. I hope this helps.

content: Since updating to android 5.0 on my nexus I can not add any notes to any of the input types anymore. Maybe app needs updating to work with 5.0 properly?
replyContent: We're sorry that there's an issue with notes on Android 5.0 - we'll look into it immediately. Re: backup - simply go to More > Backup Diary and send yourself an email with the backup attached. Then to restore it, simply open the backup file with mySymptoms and follow the prompts. I hope this helps.

content: Used it for three days... I regret purchasing this app. Interface is very complex to understand.. Having hard time figuring out how to save data in different screens. Many times ended up losing the data that was typed....
replyContent: We're sorry you find the interface confusing. Please contact us directly at issues@skygazerlabs.com to provide feedback on the interface and so that we can provide assistance.

content: Has everything I need to keep track of my illness. Thank you so much for this app. If it could improve,  I would like to see some weight gain/loss etc added in
I have a hard time understanding it! I'll continue using it.  Hopefully it will all come together for me after I use it longer.
A godsend to help me figure out my yummy troubles!!
I suspect I have Celiac's. This is exactly the tool I need to see which foods are most strongly correlated with my symptoms. Thank you!
Intuitiveness/UI-design is not its strength; with some facets, you'll spend more time than usual just figuring it out. However, the functionality is there, and the app is the best app of its kind.
replyContent: We're sorry you find the interface confusing. We have taken note of your concerns and will improve the interface in the next update. Details of the meaning of these terms can be found in More - User Guide. Thanks for your feedback.

content: Any plans to make this sync across devices? That would be extremely helpful!
replyContent: Yes, we are currently working on a sync between devices. Please keep an eye out for future updates and @mySymptomsDev on twitter for info. Thanks.

content: Good diary with basic analysis of symptoms. Well maintained with updates. Well done Stargazer.
So far has been a great way of monitoring my food intake and symptoms. Takes time to build your own favourites but worth the effort!

I've been using this app open-mindedly  for over a month. There has to be a more efficient way to enter data!My real issue is that its very hard to find common foods in the data base so u have to enter new foods and there ingredients in constantly. Its so time consuming! I just wish there was an easy way to enter info.Can there be an easier way to change the times of events? Just to add the times you have to scroll through every hour and every 59 min. Holly crap it takes forever! I'll keep trying to like it
replyContent: We're sorry you're not happy with the app. Adding ingredients can take time if they are not already available in the food database - but as the database grows this will be less of a problem. An event time defaults to the current time but can be set by scrolling or by a long hold on the time digits - a keyboard then appears. I hope this helps.

content: Best log for food sensitivities
But it has its bugs. Its crashed on me a few times and when I'm entering in some info the keyboard won't go away unless I click somewhere else and often the che check mark is out of reach.
replyContent: Hi Ray. We're very sorry the app has crashed on you and that you are experiencing a few bugs. Please submit any crash reports so that we can see the cause and fix the bugs. Also, if possible, please send us an email at issues@skygazerlabs.com with details of the other bugs so that we can find them and fix them too! Thanks for your help.

content: Love the app...but I purchased it and the first time it didn't download...so I hit refund, and then later purchased it again, and it does download. But having checked my account... I have been charged twice! And no refund given for the first one. How can I remedy this please??
replyContent: Hi Annie. We're not sure why Google Play has charged you twice. There may be delay in the refund? Please send us an email at issues@skygazerlabs.com with your purchase number for the first download and we will ensure the refund is processed. Thanks.

content: Keeps track of almost everything.  I only wish there was a list of the bad and eliminated foods or foods used sparingly and last time eaten.  Then I could better use this nice app for planning shopping trips and menus.
Will see how the results go. It is very organized and clear to see and record progress.  I like it.

Having tried a number of free aps this is the ONLY one if you're really serious about keeping a food/medication diary. Highly customisable.     One year later I'm still using the app daily and continue to find it very useful. Like the new interface/colour and additional features. Only negative is it's extremely slow responding to multiple food input on a Galaxy S4. Slow response has now been fixed.
App showed as installed on Google site but doesn't display on my device. I can't invoke the 15 minute return policy of it doesn't show up. Google help is no help.
replyContent: Hi Tracy. We're not sure why you can't see / download the app... please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com with your order number so that we can help resolve the issue with Google Play. Thanks.

content: Too busy with little availability for detail.
replyContent: We're very sorry to hear that you're not impressed with the app. We would love to understand more about your comments... please could you contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com - we would be most grateful. We can then improve the app to reflect your feedback. Thanks.

content: This app is detailed, effective, and user friendly. I have tried several dietary logs and this one will be the last one I need for fine tuning me feeling my best.

Generally I was really enjoying this app until I traveled overseas recently. Though it worked initially, it kept "checking the license". Most of the time I was offline w/o WiFi so this could've been the problem. After 5 days entering data abroad, it finally crashed and I could no longer enter info. This was serious because my doctor asked me to keep a daily food diary so my means to do this was suddenly lost. I opened the app for the first time in 10 days & it seems to work but I am missing my info.
replyContent: Hi. We're very sorry to hear that you experienced an issue with the app crashing whilst overseas. Please could you contact our support (issues@skygazerlabs.com) so that we can investigate the cause of the problem to ensure that it is fixed in future updates. Thanks.

content: Perfect for my needs.

This has been a cool app for tracking everything that goes in me and out of me.  You have to be diligent to log everything consistently.  Would be awesome if it also tracked calories!  This is my first ever review of an app...did it because it's so useful for me.  I have RA and I'm trying to eliminate certain foods and experiment with things.  Looking forward to continued improvements with this app in the future.  Peace

Great app!  I would like to  journal portion sizes also, as some foods are tolerated in smaller portions, but not large portions.   Maybe even add a bit of my finess pal's functionality such as barcode scanning and calorie and macro nutrient tracking.

The app doesn't offer a good food log. It has a lot of options but no real everyday meals. It should show nutritional values per meal, have more options (it could use USDA database) and should have a calorie counter. Good concept, not well developed
Easy to use. Great ability to document and track symptoms around food and bowel and pain, etc.  The tool analysis is weak and meaningless.

The depth and scope of data that can be captured goes far beyond any other app of this type. For monitoring and reporting this is a must have, it gives a great insight into suspected causes of problems.
Info ahead of time helps cut down on the wait and see attitude of some Dr's. Hopefully will get to the root of the problem sooner!
Just what the doctor ordered-literally.  I was diagnosed with something nasty today so I'm waiting for an appointment with a dietitian so this app will be so useful. Thank you x

I was looking for an app where I can easily keep track of what I ate and then make note of the symptoms. But this app is too complicted and not very well designed. Too many menues and categories. Have a typical breakfast of eggs, bacon, potatoes, and toast, with a glass of OJ, and you'll spend 10 minutes scrolling through the menues to find all those items. Forget anything more complicated. It just takes too long finding all the items. I ended up uninstalling it since I just never used it.
replyContent: We're sorry to hear that you don't like the app. Searching for foods should be straightforward - simply tap add on the menu bar, select an event type (e.g. breakfast), then add content by searching to food database and tapping on the item you require. Please contact us at enhancements@skygazerlabs.com with any suggested improvements. Thanks.

content: I am being tested for stomach problems at  present.. suspected chrones. Some days worse than others. This app has given me an opportunity to record everything to give my consultant a head start. It will probably cut out the awkward "I'm not sure" answers and help get me back on track. Well worth money so far .
It has only been a week but I love how this app is compiling the results instead of me trying to remember what the problem could be.
I just got this recently and already love it. It's easy to use and is very organized. It's nice to be able to break everything down and get to the bottom of your problem.

While there is a serious lack of foods found in the US, and some less than helpful analysis  functions, it is still a very helpful app and at worst is a good food diary to show to the doctor. Worth it, but I hope it will get a lot more comprehensive in the future.
I live on mobile devices and this is just terrible. The more I evaluated this app the worse it worked.
replyContent: Hi Tim. We're sorry to hear that you don't like the app and would be very interested to understand why. Please feel free to contact us directly at issues@skygazerlabs.com. Thanks.

content: This it's a great app. It would get 5 stars if you could input your portions, for example, coffee 1 cup or 2 cups. My nutritionist wants serving sizes when I turn in my report and it's extra work to write it all in the notes.  If you could add that I would definitely give 5 stars.

You're supposed to be able to enter what you ate easily with this app, but not once did I actually find what I ate when I searched! I was trying to track things like cold cereal with milk, yogurt, sweet peppers, and chicken sandwich, so nothing too absurd! It wasn't worth my time to manually enter everything I agree, so this was just a waste of money.
replyContent: Hi Molly. I'm sorry you are unhappy with the app. The app description clearly indicates that only a small database of foods is included - you will need to add foods to your diary - but it's as simple as typing the food name and tapping the add button. Please contact us directly at issues@skygazerlabs.com if you wish to receive a refund.

content: So far so good, I have had this app for a few days and it has worked very well. Key to having this work accurately for you is to include the ingredients!
The food library is exceptionally limited so my daily food log is always going to be inaccurate. Waste of money.
replyContent: Hi Eryn. The food database contains a few thousand basic ingredients - if you can't find what you are looking for, simply tap 'Add' to add the item to the database. If you are still unhappy, then please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com. Thanks.

content: Just purchased this app and for some reason, after I write a note, I cannot find where to view it anywhere. I can only view food and symptoms. I rely on the notes option because not all symptoms I'm trying to monitor are listed. Please include joint pain in update.
replyContent: Hi Nicole. Notes are at the bottom of diary entries - please scroll down the screen. Also, you can add your own symptoms by adding a new symptom event then scrolling down to 'Organize symptoms'. Then tap the + button and enter the required symptom name. Then hit 'Done'. If you require further support, go to More > Report an issue. Thanks.

content: I tried several apps to detect  my food allergy. This is the best. Would be great to add a sensation of well being.
I like to see developers that can create new software, with new ideas and concepts.  Exactly what I needed.

Even as the best app, it still could be greatly enhanced with the addition of a separate category for daily blood pressure, BMI, readings, known allergens, and vitamins/supplements.  Also full ingredient detail with each entry should be somewhere because it is the ingredients often that cause the problem.  And, if all entries for each category ( medication, dinner, exercise cetera) showed up under the diary under just once for the day ( ie. the way symptoms are shown) , it would be far less confusing.
Have used this app for 1 year and it is so convenient.

This is just what I need. I'm able to record my foods, medications, and symptoms.  I do notice some foods I try to type in are not included in the list so I have to create new foods. Been having frequent headaches, migraines and other symptoms, so I'm hoping this will help me figure out if certain foods/ingredients are causing them. Thank you!

I got this app planning to start an elimination diet. So far I'm impressed. I agree with another reviewer, I'd love the option to add family members and be able to track myself and my kid. I'd be willing to pay more to upgrade to a family edition.

This app was clearly written outside the US because some of the included foods are not common here, and some common foods are not included. As an example, the cheeses include many typical British styles, but not Swiss or cheddar. Adding new items is easy, and being able to put in ingredients is nice for drilling down to the the base of problems.
This is exactly what I was looking for.
I would find this app much more useful if it had reminders such as for scheduled meds or water intake and etc. Would be a 5 if I had those options.

I recently purchased this app and I'm finding it highly useful and practical. I'm using it to help determine food allergies and the detailed level of foods, symptoms, etc. are already giving me good direction. I particularly like that I can include physical activities and readily link that to how I feel.

I really like this app. It has a nice, clean interface, is easy to use, and very customisable with lots of different options.   A few requests - would it be possible to increase the maximum number of characters that can be entered when creating a new food or drink item? Also, are there any plans to add an option to select quantities - for example, if I eat 2 slices of toast, I either have to add two entries for 'toast' or create a new one called 'toast x 2'. Thanks.

I only just started it today and I'm already struggling with this app. My main symptom and the reason I bought this app is because I get hives everyday. Hives is not an option in symptoms. I'm shocked by how small the list of symptoms is. I also noticed there were no mental symptoms (irritability, hyperactivity, etc.) I also wish I could include amounts of things ingested. If I react from a tiny bite of strawberries, I'd like the app to be able to connect it. These things would be a great improvement, IMHO.
replyContent: You can add symptoms as follows: add a new symptom event, scroll down the list of symptoms until you see 'Organize symptoms' - tap it. Now add a new symptom using the '+' button on the action bar - a new row appears with 'New symptom' - simply tap on it and change it's name as required. When done, press 'Done' on the action bar. I hope this helps.

content: Pizza isn't a standard food, so it wouldbe nice to have that. I like the app so far.  :)
Great app, easy to use. Can keep track of both eating habits and symptoms and see both at a glance. Very useful for finding patterns in IBS and other GI ailments.
New user so only two days in. It does what it says on the tin. My only requirement is that it records information that I can present to my Doctor. So far so good
Haven't tested the symptoms section yet, but app worth 5 stars as a food diary alone.
Keep the updates coming :)

I don't noramly give feedback on apps or even pay for them.. But this app is worth every penny as has improved my life greatly ... I use to log everything into an excel spreadsheet ... Worst idea ever this makes recording your diet and symptoms so easy thank you who ever wrote this app

I purchased this app on Nov 14th. It worked fine until today with a licence expired messages. 2.99$ for 14 day use??? Frustrating. Will request a refund from Google if not fixed. U pay and get this. They have to change the licensing model. It has to WORK when U pay for software. And YES the phone is online. But even OFFLINE it should work.
replyContent: Hi Michelle, I'm sorry you are having problems with the license. The license will not expire. The problem appears to be that the app has attempted to connect to Google's license server and failed. Please contact us at issues@skygazerlabs.com for further assistance. It is not our licensing model - you only purchase the app once.

content: We have eosinophilic esophagitis and this program is superb at tracking symptoms and keeping track of food.

This is a good app to list everything you do, eat and symptoms you are having to find the culprit. It also gives out a form you can take to your doctor which greatly helps as mostly your doctor will not find out without such info.
works great!
this app is way more complete than any free app I found. you have to put in everything you eat but the better job the better it works,
Good so far. It would be handy to include wee and quality and volume of wee in the group of outcomes you can select. Very easy and clear to use so far. Money well spent. Thanks
Love this app. I would highly recommend it for anyone with: allergies, body pain, hsp, anxiety, headaches, etc. It helps to track what may be triggering the problems. :)
Great i use it all the time

I love this app! It is friendly, easy to use and very intuitive.  I searched and tried a few app and this one is by far the best app to record your food intake and associated symptoms.  Would be nice to have the addition of trigger foods like: food additives, pesticides, histamine,  shady vegetables,  Gluten ... Thank you!

Lots of nice features. Quite intuitive. It would be nice if the contents of the food already existed - including allergens that links different foods that one would not immediately think of. And that way every user would not have to do it to get the benefits
Geeat app, great features, usable layout. My main complaint is that I wish I could track information for multiple people in my family. :(
Simple, yet includes all the features I need.  I can quickly track my symptoms and diet while on the go.  Well worth the cost.
A great app. Hundreds of foods and etc. But only four stars because it doesnt explain things like the colored dots that are used after adding the food youve eaten.	Keep up good work.
This is a powerful and flexible analysis tool. I wish thw documentation was better and included a walk through tutorial.
replyContent: Hi Ben. It's great to hear that you like the app. We're currently working on the next update and will improve the documentation and include a walk through. In the meantime, if you have any questions, please feel free to email us at support@skygazerlabs.com. Thanks.

content: Really useful little app for tracking symptoms and causes... not just for allergies. Also great support... asked for some new features and got a response saying they were planning to add in an update... great news.
Love it, easy to use, favorites, auto calculates likely hood of triggers to give an idea what to avoid. Wish it had a section for blood sugar, blood pressure
I wish I found this app a long time ago!
I have to do a food & symptom diary for my doctor. This works great so far.

This app is really well thought out and has proved really useful in identifying problem foods for me.   I researched a lot of similar apps and this was the only one that ticked all the boxes.  The dev is actively seeking improvements and continues to enhance this terrific app.
Enough features for what  I need and simple enough to let me put my information in quickly the first time I use it. Love this app!
*Top notch user interface.  *Not too complicated yet rich in features.  *backups *option to e-mail reports *add your own "stuff" *and more
It's simple and fairly easy to use. I just wish there was a widget so I could view quickly or add an entry quickly.
I like this app so far. I would love seeing the ability to add the amount of medication and mgs or oz you are taking and be able to see results of this.

I'd been wanting a better way to track corelations of symptoms and causes, and the flexibility of the customizable features does just that. Love the graphs, the automatic saving of customized entries ("gluten", etc ) & the ease of precision. I'd like to customize the icon of new categories, and to be able to remove them. But still. Buy it. Use it. :)
Can't figure out how to record symptoms.   The user guide is not helpful in this respect. How do you put these in?
replyContent: You can add symptoms as follows: when adding a new symptom event, scroll down the list of symptoms until you see 'Organize symptoms' - tap it. Now you can add a new symptom using the '+' button on the action bar - a new row appears with 'New symptom' - simply tap on it and change it's name as required. When done, press 'Done' on the action bar.

content: Would love to add family members on same app so I can track their intolerances as well. Backup/Synchronization between devices would be highly appreciated. Some more comprehensive, printable analysis reports & graphs that can be given to physicians would be helpful. e.g. symptoms report that indicates food items that contain triggers.

I've tried a few food journals but this one is prefect for what I need. It's easy and intuitive to use and the graphics are pleasing. I only wish I found it 6 months ago when I started my elimination diet!
This dependable and user friendly app not only helps you identify which items are likely linked with a symptom, but also which ones are not. That is every bit as helpful.

It takes a little bit to get used to.  Adding items are easy, however time consuming, but once you add in all the items you regularly eat it is very quick to add foods.  Love the symptom patterns.  I have been dealing with unexplained stomach pain for nearly 10 years and am hoping this will give me an idea as to the causes.  Maybe. :/
Very nice app, seems pretty well thought out.  Dev was very quick to respond to my notice of a minor quirk.  For the cost and functionality I think It's a great value.
I've been needing to do a food diary for a while and hadn't thought to look for an app. This has been really use full especially the HTML output, thanks.

Works great, just remember to fill it in!  Only problem is the bowel movement bit - it uses bristol scale but does not analyse according to the different levels, it puts all levels together in one symptom, separate them out tech guys as different symptoms and then it would be perfect! Eg we want to know what causes the bad stuff!  Ick, sorry to be blunt, blushing

I had no idea something like was out there. I have GERD. Bad. I had it under control for more than 10 years, but now it's back. Since I don't want to eat/live/drink like a purist, I have to figure out what the patterns are before I have these awful attacks so I can remove the triggers. This app is going well so far. I'm having a little bit of a hard time getting into the habit of entering every single thing every day, but that's operator error, not app error. :) Wouldn't mind if there was just a website functionality so I could enter stuff from my laptop or desktop. It is so much faster than my phone or tablet.
Good, but farfrom perfect.  Does not allow variables in and limited symptoms. Allowing new types of symptoms to be added would be a great help. It would definitely move it towards being perfect.
replyContent: Hi. You can add new symptoms by tapping 'Organize symptoms...' when adding a new symptom event. On the 'Symptoms' screen tap '+' on the actionbar to add a new symptom. Enter the name of the symptom, tap 'Done'. Now you can use the symptom in your diary. Also add foods/items to your diary from either a diary event or using the 'Organizer' tab.

content: Add your food diary, symptoms, and environment, and the app will try to identify what is making you I'll.

After trying other Allergy apps and failing miserably, found this and it really works well! Very easy to navigate through and customize. Very worth while in trying to figure out what's trying to kill me! Worth every penny of it's cost!

I only downloaded it today so only time will tell if it will help me with my digestive issues.  But so far it seems like a fantastic app.  I love that it not only lets you record everything you eat and any major stress or environmental factor, as well as your symptoms, but it is also made to look for patterns in the long term. I am so excited to keep using this and see if it can help me figure anything out! I've gone through tons of doctors but never have figured out what's wrong. I think this might help!
excellent

Just installed. Very easy to add and edit foods and symptoms. Developer was super friendly and responsive to my questions. Analysis functionality looks sleek and powerful - I hope they prove useful. Just missing export to CSV and report with analysis but developer said they are on  future roadmap. It is the first app I ever bought and so far I am a fan. 1 bug is when adding new symptom to bottom of the list cannot see the text because blocked by softkeyboard (on galaxy s3).
Nice
Amazing! Just what I need to track anything and everything physiological about me.

I'm having a lot of health issues linked to what I eat and this app is proving to be a life saver for me to be able to avoid pain. If I have a question about anything I eat I can just check really quickly. It is helping me nail down problem foods that I hadn't even considered. I love that I can add any symptoms I want. Thank you so much for this app!
I do wish that the back button on the phone was used in the normal way, to undo. At the moment, pressing the back arrow button exits the app.

The app is pretty easy to use. Limited in foods which are listed, but it is easy to add new ones, (once you figgure out how). The analyze feature I'm not sure about yet, perhaps I just need more data. But it makes it easy to keep track of what you eat & if you have good or bad reactions, which is what I needed.

I don't agree with the 'hard to use' comments.  The app seems intuitive to me.  (Full disclosure, I'm an engineer so that may something to do with it.). Functionality is very complete. Database not huge, but that isn't the intent.
I tried to enter English Muffins, cream cheese, and ribs. None of these are in the database :(
replyContent: If a food isn't in the database, simply tap the 'Add new item...' option or the '+' button on the action bar. The food will then be added to the database and will be available for use from then on. I hope this helps.

content: Great app, developer very responsive to feedback and keeps making it even better. It is very useful in figuring out what specific ingredients aggravate symptoms.
It is a nice concept, but adding food and drinks is not easy.  Adding meds to list is difficult also.
replyContent: To add foods / meds simply type their name in the search bar and tap the 'Add new item...' option or the '+' button on the action bar. They will then be added to the database and will be available for use from then on. I hope this helps.

content: This is a well thought out app. I'm recommending it to anyone who has issues they need help identifying or controlling. I hope you continue improving it. I'm sure there are more functions that can be added.
Love the way this works. Once favourites set up it is so easy to use
Some improvements can still be made in terms of ease of use but overall this has been super useful for me in helping me as I adjust to having multiple food allergies.

So useful, not all that user friendly but once you've used it once or twice it is easy enough to understand. They really have thought of everything. Super simple and intuitive, I wish this was around 10 years ago. Well worth the money, no other app can compare to this.

Really not much analysis. Is better than other diary apps to record information. So it got two instead of one star. We are looking for trends in symptoms relative to certain foods. This app doesn't do that at all.
Deleting my previous days food diary so can't revert back to it and listing a medication I help to combat nausea as a high risk for nausea....something wrong!
There was a little learning curve with this one, but I picked it up on about 5 min of trial and error.  Its got everything I was looking for.
Very limited instructions.  I still can't figure out how to rate the foods according to symptoms (the very purpose of the app). I will be deleting it.

I found it confusing at first, but the examples on the website were enough to get me going, now I really like it. I'd like to see a better video, going just a bit more slowly and without the ugly music to be more helpful to newcomers.

Haven't tried the charts yet, but so far very useful. Would like to be able to make general day notes incl. weather, location, activities as these seem to affect my allergies. Only one thing needs fixing- on galaxy s3 I can't scroll when the keyboard is up so I can't see what I am typing.
Easy to use, missing a lot of common foods but its easy to add them
Excellent app! Clean, concise, and I had no trouble with the learning curve. Highly recommend!
This app was perfect for anyone who needs a symptom diary etc. You can program meals and common ingredients in foods. Any issues with app and very fast response from developer. And it's free
Unfortunately it is not very intuitive and when I want to type, the keyboard covers the typing area so I can't see what I am typing.

I downloaded this app and it kept crashing, so I contacted the developer, and he pushed out a fix within a day. Amazing! It works perfectly now. I'm looking forward to getting more details entered in order to get a useful analysis. What a great app for anyone trying to sift through complex symptoms! Kudos to the developer for great work on this app. Definitely worth paying for.
Force closes constant with every update.. app would work better if it took meds into consideration, doesn't seem to pop up as a trigger for symptoms?
Not very intuitive for a new user. The user guide helped but it still took awhile to figure things out.
Had one problem. Reported it. Fixed the next day. Incredible. And it is exactly what I've been looking for to track my food related symptoms since going through cancer treatment.

Has really helped improve my life. I've had various problems with different kinds of foods, but this application has enabled me to isolate the culprits. I've since changed my lifestyle and feel so much better for it.

It is taking time for me to get used to using this app but now im getting used to it I really like it! Only issue is when I type notes my diary entry the keyboard covers the text box so I can't see what I'm typing! I'm looking forward to seeing how the reports look after I've been using this a while.

Seems like a good app so far but I have only had it for a day.  Not the most intuitive and a bit clunky to add foods and ingredients.  But if you read the instructions you'll get the hang of it.  Might rate this app agaain in a few months after using it daily.
Simple, intuitive, thorough, customizable and helpful! This is just what i have been looking for to help me track my ibs symptoms! Thanks so much!
